CustExpIntlTransfSetup.name: CustExpIntlTransfSetup
CustExpIntlTransfSetup.description: Stores information for different data sources that are processed for customer insights. This object is available in API version 65.0 and later.

DataSourceChannelName.description: The name of the associated communication channel, such as Web, Email, Chat, or Voice.

DataSourceChannelType.description: Specifies the channel type as standard or custom.

IsDataProcessingPaused.description: Indicates whether data processing for the channel is temporarily paused (true). Use this field to control channel operations without deactivating the channel.

IsEnabled.description: Indicates whether the channel is active for processing data (true).

LastReferencedDate.description: Date and time when the current user last viewed or modified this record, a record related to this record, or a list view. If this value is null, the current user has never viewed or modified a record related to this object.

LastViewedDate.description: Date and time when the current user last viewed or modified this record. If this value is null, the current user has never viewed or modified this record.

Name.description: The name of the Customer Experience Intelligence Transformer Setup record.

ProcessingStartDate.description: The date to start processing data in the specified communication channel.
